Preamble (Gratitude + Intent)

This project is indebted to the SQLite project: technically, and
philosophically. SQLite demonstrated that small, careful software can power a
large fraction of civilization, and it did so while keeping reuse friction as
close to zero as the law allows.

Intent: Free Access, Free Use

Our intent is that all original code and improvements in this repository be
freely accessible as possible.

In that spirit, and in honor of SQLite, we include the SQLite Blessing:

May you do good and not evil.
May you find forgiveness for yourself and forgive others.
May you share freely, never taking more than you give.

Legal Reality: Jurisdictions and Policies Vary

Some jurisdictions do not fully recognize public-domain dedications, and some
users require an OSI-approved license for compliance, redistribution, or
internal policy. Therefore, in addition to the blessing above, we
offer this project under a quad-license so you can choose what fits your
situation.

